%F A387574 a(n) = (n^2 + 3*n + 6)/2 = A152948(n+3) if the maximal order of the field Q[x]/(x^3 - n*x^2 - (n+3)*x - 1) is generated by a root of x^3 - n*x^2 - (n+3)*x - 1 [Kala-Tinková, Section 7.2].
%F A387574 a(n) = (n^2 + 39*n + 36)/18 if n > 3 and if the order Z[rho] generated by a root rho of x^3 - n*x^2 - (n+3)*x - 1 has index 3 in the maximal order of Q[x]/(x^3 - n*x^2 - (n+3)*x - 1) [Gil-Muñoz-Tinková, Theorem 1.1].
%e A387574 For n = 0, the corresponding simplest cubic field is given by the defining polynomial f(x) = x^3 - 3*x - 1. All additively indecomposable elements of K are 1, -rho^2 + 4, and rho^2 + rho + 1 (up to multiplication by totally positive units), thus a(0) = 3.
%e A387574 For n = 1, the corresponding simplest cubic field is given by the defining polynomial f(x) = x^3 - x^2 - 4*x - 1.  All additively indecomposables elements of K are 1, rho^2 + rho + 1, rho^2 - 2*rho, -rho^2 + rho + 5, and rho + 2 (up to multiplication by totally positive units), thus a(1) = 5.
%e A387574 For n = 2, the corresponding simplest cubic field is given by the defining polynomial f(x) = x^3 - 2*x^2 - 5*x - 1.  All additively indecomposables elements of K are 1, rho^2 - 3*rho, -rho^2 + 2*rho + 6, rho + 2, 2*rho^2 - 5*rho - 1, rho^2 - 2*rho, 2*rho^2 - 6*rho - 1, and -4*rho^2 + 9*rho + 19 (up to multiplication by totally positive units), thus a(2) = 8.
